- autocategorize rules
- fix graphs

## Bugs fixed (2026-07-18)
- [x] Chart RangeError (Chart.js walking Livewire proxy) + canvas resize-after-update regression
- [x] Category drill-down chart/list going empty on click (Category::descendants() pluck('id') bug)
- [x] "Pull Data" button not refreshing the nested transactions component
- [x] Plaid "Link Institution" button dead after navigating via a wire:navigate link (needed hard refresh)

## Still open, not yet fixed
- [ ] Null-pointer risk: app/Actions/UpdateAccountTransactionsAction.php:39 —
      `$transaction->original_category_id = $category->id` runs even when
      `$category` can be null
- [ ] composer audit: 21 advisories across transitive deps (guzzle, symfony/yaml,
      etc.) — likely fixed by a plain `composer update` (no constraint changes)
- [ ] composer: safe patch/minor updates available (pint, flux, volt, rector,
      larastan, ...); Laravel 13 / Pest 4 / Boost 2.x are separate deliberate bumps
- [ ] npm: vite, tailwindcss, axios, autoprefixer, concurrently, lightningcss
      behind their semver-compatible "wanted" versions
- [ ] No test coverage for OriginalCategory, upsertPlaidCategory(),
      resolveCategory(), or the chart pipeline

## Categorization UX pass (2026-07-18)
- [x] Optimistic category save — pill shows instantly (pulsing) on click via a
      client-side categoryLookup, $wire.saveCategory() called directly (not
      through a dispatch/listener round trip) so it returns a promise to
      reconcile/rollback on. Replaces the old modal Save button entirely —
      picking a category now saves immediately.
- [x] Replaced the flat category <select> in the assign-category modal with a
      searchable/filterable list (client-side filter over categoryList, no
      server round trip per keystroke)
- [x] Merchant-based category suggestions — computed per-page in with() via
      merchantSuggestions(), surfaced as an inline "+ Category?" quick-apply
      chip next to uncategorized transactions, and pinned at the top of the
      modal when opened via "+". Groundwork for future auto-categorization.
- [ ] Explicitly deprioritized for now: favorites / most-used quick-pick chips
- [ ] Add a way to create a new category directly from the "assign category"
      popup (ideally a nested modal), so a brand-new category can be created
      and assigned to the transaction in one flow
- [ ] The delete-category (x) affordance on existing pills relies on
      mouseover/mouseout (x-show="over") — doesn't work on touch/mobile since
      there's no hover state. Needs a tap-friendly alternative on small screens.

